	recognising the applicable tax rate at the point when the timing difference is expected to reverse. A further change to the UK corporation tax rate was announced in the Chancellors Budget during the year ended 31 March 2016. The
	announcement included a reduction in the UK corporation tax rate to 17 per cent from 1 April 2020. As the change to 17 per cent had not been substantively enacted at the balance sheet date, its effects are not included in these
	financial statements.








