Light Commercial Vehicles (including pick-ups)    Under SIAM classifications, commercial vehicles with a GVW of up to 7.5
metric tonnes are classified as light commercial vehicles, or LCVs. We are the leading LCV manufacturer in India. For fiscal 2004, our LCV sales accounted for approximately 49.6% of the domestic unit sales of LCVs by all Indian manufacturers.
   Our principal LCV in terms of sales is the TATA 407. Through
March 2004, we sold approximately 350,000 units since its introduction in 1986. We also re-launched a new pick-up truck in fiscal 2003 – Tata 207DI – that has gained considerable customer acceptance and has enabled us to make significant
gains in our LCV market share. In our efforts to focus on fully built vehicles, we recently launched the City Ride, a complete bus built on an LCV platform. All our LCV models comply with Euro I and II emission norms as applicable in India or
international markets in which they are sold.    The following
