   Medium and Heavy Commercial
Vehicles    Under SIAM classifications, commercial vehicles
with a GVW above 7.5 metric tonnes are classified as medium and heavy commercial vehicles, or MHCVs. We are the leading MHCV manufacturer in India. For fiscal 2004, our MHCVs achieved a market share of approximately 64.0% of the domestic unit sales
of MHCVs by all Indian manufacturers.    Our MHCVs have a wide
range of applications, in particular for long haul and container traffic movement and use on rough terrain, and are generally configured as trucks, tippers, buses, tankers, tractors or concrete mixers. We offer three engine options in this range
– 697 (developed in-house), Cummins 6BT and CNG. All our MHCV models comply with Euro I and II emission norms as applicable in India or international markets in which they are sold.   
26 


