   Valuation allowances have been created for deferred tax assets arising at subsidiaries that are making losses and that do not expect a return to tax profitability in the foreseeable future. Deferred tax assets and liabilities are offset if
they arise in the same legal entity and taxing jurisdiction but not otherwise.    Under the Indian Income Tax Act, 1961, unabsorbed business losses expire eight years after the year in which they originate whereas
unabsorbed depreciation allowances can be carried forward indefinitely. In respect of a foreign subsidiary in Singapore the unabsorbed business losses can be carried forward indefinitely unless there is a substantial change in the ownership.
  
